P1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-88"}], ["88."]}, "  Any person who, without lawful authority or reasonable excuse, in any way intentionally or negligently obstructs the free passage along a road shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Lighting fires or discharging fireworks near a road", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-89"}], ["89."]}, "  Where—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-89-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["any person, without lawful authority or reasonable excuse, lights a fire or discharges a firework within 15 metres of the centre of a road; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-89-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["in consequence any person or traffic using the road is injured, endangered or interrupted,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegText"}], ["the first-mentioned person shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Pitching stalls or offering things for sale on a road", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-90"}], ["90."]}, "—(1) Any person who, on a road, without lawful authority—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-90-1-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["pitches a booth, stall or stand; or"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-90-1-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["subject to paragraph (2), offers or exposes anything for sale, or for the purpose of sale,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) A person shall not be guilty of an offence under paragraph (1)(b) if he offers or exposes anything for sale in circumstances where, by virtue of", {"span", [{"class", "LegChangeDelimiter"}], ["["]}, {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867751"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867751"}], ["F145"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegAddition"}], [" section 2 of the Street Trading Act (Northern Ireland) 2001, he would not be required to obtain a street trading licence or a temporary licence under that Act"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegChangeDelimiter"}], ["]"]}, " authorising him so to do.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Any person convicted of an offence under paragraph (1) shall, within such period as the court may allow, remove from the road any booth, stall or stand, or any thing offered or exposed for sale, and if he fails to do so he shall be guilty of an offence and be liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding one-tenth of level 2 on the standard scale for each day upon which that failure continues.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Where a person who has been convicted of an offence under paragraph (1) becomes liable to prosecution for an offence under paragraph (3), the Department may itself do anything which he has failed to do, and may recover from him any expenses thereby reasonably incurred by it.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Where—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-90-5-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["any thing has been removed by the Department under paragraph (4); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-90-5-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["it has not been recovered by its owner within 21 days from the day on which it was removed,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["the Department may dispose of it in such manner as the Department thinks fit.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) Where any thing is disposed of by sale under paragraph (5) the expenses of removal and sale shall be defrayed out of the proceeds thereof and the balance of the proceeds (if any) shall be given to the owner if known and if not shall be applied in the same manner as is provided for with respect to fines by section 20 of the Administration of Justice Act (Northern Ireland) 1954", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867771"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867771"}], ["F146"]}, ".\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(7) Where the Department disposes of any thing under paragraph (5)—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-90-7-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["by sale and the proceeds are not sufficient to defray the Department's expenses; or"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-90-7-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["in some manner other than by sale,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["the Department may recover from the owner thereof any expenses reasonably incurred by it in removing and disposing of the thing.\r"]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867751"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867751"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F145"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/nia/2001/8"}], ["2001 c. 8 (NI)"]}]}]}]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867771"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867771"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F146"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/apni/1954/9"}], ["1954 c. 9 (N.I.)"]}]}]}]}]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Encamping on a road", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-91"}], ["91."]}, "—(1) Any person who without reasonable excuse encamps, or maintains an encampment consisting of a tent, caravan or any other form of shelter, on a road shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) Where a person has contravened paragraph (1), the Department may serve on him a notice requiring him to remove the encampment within such period as may be specified in the notice.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Where, on a complaint made by the Department, a court of summary jurisdiction is satisfied that a person—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-91-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["has contravened paragraph (1); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-91-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["has failed to comply with a notice served on him under paragraph (2),"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["the court may make an order requiring that person to remove the encampment.\r"]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Playing games on a road", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-92"}], ["92."]}, "  Any person who plays a game on a road to the danger of any person using the road, shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Animals on a road", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-93"}], ["93."]}, "—(1) Any person who—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-93-1-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["turns loose any animal onto a road; or"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-93-1-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["by negligence or illusage in driving any animal on a road causes any person to be injured or property to be damaged by such animal,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) If any animal is at any time found wandering or lying on or at the side of the road, the keeper thereof shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) For the purposes of paragraph (2) it shall be a defence for the keeper of an animal to show—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-93-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["that he took reasonable precautions to prevent the animal from wandering onto the road; or"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-93-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["that the animal had wandered onto the road from unfenced land and that—"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP4Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP4No"}, {"id", "article-93-3-b-i"}], ["(i)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP4Text"}], ["the land is situated in an area where fencing is not customary, and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP4Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP4No"}, {"id", "article-93-3-b-ii"}], ["(ii)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP4Text"}], ["that he had a right to place the animal on that land."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) In this Article—\r"]}, {"ul", [{"class", "LegTabbed LegUnorderedList"}], [{"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“animal” means any horse (including pony, ass and mule), cattle, sheep, goat or swine or any deer not in the wild state; and\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“keeper” has the same meaning as in Article 2(2)(b) of the Animals (Northern Ireland) Order 1976", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867781"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867781"}], ["F147"]}, ".\r"]}]}]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867781"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867781"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F147"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/nisi/1976"}], ["1976 NI 13"]}]}]}]}]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Depositing of things on roads", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-94"}], ["94."]}, "—(1) Any person who deposits, or causes or permits to be deposited, building materials, rubble, rubbish, compost, dung or any other thing whatsoever on a road in such a position as to cause, or be likely to cause, any obstruction or danger, shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) Where—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-94-2-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["a person deposits, or causes or permits to be deposited on a road any thing mentioned in paragraph (1); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-94-2-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the Department considers that the thing in question constitutes a danger to persons using the road,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["then (whether or not proceedings are instituted for an offence under that paragraph) the Department may remove the thing or take such other steps as are necessary to obviate the danger.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Where—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-94-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["a person is convicted of an offence under paragraph (1); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-94-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["he does not, within such period as the court may allow, remove the thing in question from the road,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["the Department may itself remove that thing from the road.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) The Department may dispose of any thing removed by it under paragraph (2) or (3) in such manner as it thinks fit.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Where any thing is disposed of by sale under paragraph (4) the expenses of removal and sale shall be defrayed out of the proceeds thereof and the balance of the proceeds (if any) shall be given to the owner if known and if not shall be applied in the same manner as is provided for with respect to fines by section 20 of the Administration of Justice Act (Northern Ireland) 1954", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867791"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867791"}], ["F148"]}, ".\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) Where the Department disposes of any thing under paragraph (4)—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-94-6-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["by sale and the proceeds are not sufficient to defray the Department's expenses; or"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-94-6-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["in some manner other than by sale,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["the Department may recover from the person who deposited that thing on the road any expenses reasonably incurred by it in removing and disposing of the thing.\r"]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867791"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867791"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F148"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/apni/1954/9"}], ["1954 c. 9 (N.I.)"]}]}]}]}]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Matter spilling or flowing onto roads from vehicles or adjoining land", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-95"}], ["95."]}, "—(1) Any person who, being in charge of a vehicle on a road, permits any solid or liquid matter from the vehicle, or being carried on the vehicle, to drop or be spilled on the carriageway of a road in such quantity as to create, or be likely to create, a danger or substantial inconvenience to persons using the road, shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) For the purposes of paragraph (1)—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-95-2-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["a person is in charge of a vehicle if, as owner or otherwise, he has immediate charge or control of the vehicle, or if he is entitled to give orders to the person having such charge or control; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-95-2-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["“vehicle” includes anything towed by a vehicle."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Any person who intentionally or recklessly permits any filth, dirt, lime, oil or other offensive matter to run or flow onto a road from any adjoining land shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Where—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-95-4-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["a person permits any matter to drop or be spilled on, or run or flow onto, a road in contravention of paragraph (1) or (3); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-95-4-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["does not remove that matter as soon as is practicable,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["then (whether or not proceedings are instituted for an offence under paragraph (1) or (3)) the Department may—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP4Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP4No"}, {"id", "article-95-4-i"}], ["(i)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP4Text"}], ["remove that matter from the road, and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP4Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP4No"}, {"id", "article-95-4-ii"}], ["(ii)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP4Text"}], ["recover from that person any expenses thereby reasonably incurred by it."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) The Department may dispose of any matter removed by it under paragraph (4) in such manner as it thinks fit.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) Where a person is convicted of an offence under paragraph (3), the Department may serve a notice on him requiring him to carry out such works as are necessary to prevent further matter running or flowing onto a road in contravention of that paragraph.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(7) Article 58 applies to a notice served under paragraph (6) as it applies to a notice served as mentioned in paragraph (1) of that Article.\r"]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Control of builders' skips", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-96"}], ["96."]}, "—(1) The owner of a builder's skip who causes or permits it to be deposited in such a position on a road as to cause or be likely to cause a danger to persons using or entering the road shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) The Department may make regulations specifying conditions subject to which builders' skips may be deposited on roads, and, in particular, conditions relating to—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the siting of skips,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the marking on skips of the name and telephone number or address of the owner thereof,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["their dimensions,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-d"}], ["(d)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the manner in which they are to be coated with paint or other material for the purpose of making them immediately visible to oncoming traffic,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-e"}], ["(e)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the care and disposal of their contents,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-f"}], ["(f)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the times at and manner in which they are to be lighted or guarded,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-96-2-g"}], ["(g)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["their removal."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Regulations made under paragraph (2) may specify positions and circumstances in which the owner of a builder's skip shall not cause or permit it to be deposited on roads without obtaining the consent of the Department.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Where the owner of a builder's skip contravenes any regulations made under paragraph (2), he shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Where the commission by any person of an offence under paragraph (1) or (4) is due to the act or default of some other person, that other person may be charged with and convicted of the offence by virtue of this paragraph whether or not proceedings are taken against the first-mentioned person.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) In any proceedings for an offence under paragraph (1) or (4) it shall, subject to paragraph (7), be a defence for the person charged to prove that the commission of the offence was due to the act or default of another person and that he took all reasonable precautions and exercised all due diligence to avoid the commission of such an offence by himself or any person under his control.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(7) A person charged with an offence under paragraph (1) or (4) shall not, without leave of the court, be entitled to rely on the defence provided by paragraph (6) unless, within a period ending 7 days before the hearing, he has served on the complainant a notice in writing giving such information identifying or assisting in the identification of that other person as was then in his possession.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(8) The person to whom a consent is issued under this Article in respect of a builder's skip shall indemnify the Department against any claim in respect of injury, damage or loss arising out of the deposit or presence of that skip on a road, other than a claim in respect of injury, damage or loss which is attributable to the negligence of the Department.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(9) Nothing in this Article shall be taken as authorising the creation of a nuisance or danger to persons using or entering a road.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(10) In this Article and", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867801"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867801"}], ["F149"]}, " in Article 97—\r"]}, {"ul", [{"class", "LegTabbed LegUnorderedList"}], [{"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“builder's skip” means a container designed to be carried on a vehicle and to be placed on a road or other land for the storage of builders' materials, or for the removal and disposal of rubble, waste, household and other rubbish or earth;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“constable” means a member of the Royal Ulster Constabulary or the Royal Ulster Constabulary Reserve;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“owner”, in relation to a builder's skip which is the subject of a hiring agreement, being an agreement for a hiring of not less than one month, or a hire purchase agreement, means the person in possession of the skip under that agreement;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“police officer” means a member of the Royal Ulster Constabulary not below the rank of Inspector.\r"]}]}]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867801"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867801"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F149"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], ["prosp. subst. by ", {"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/nisi/1995"}], ["1995 NI 19"]}]}]}]}]}, {"h4", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Removal of builders' skips", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-97"}], ["97."]}, "—(1) Where a builder's skip has been deposited on a road an officer authorised by the Department or a constable in uniform may require the owner of the skip to remove or reposition it, or cause it to be removed or repositioned, notwithstanding that the skip has been deposited on the road in accordance with conditions specified in regulations made under Article 96(2).\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) A person required to remove or reposition, or cause to be removed or repositioned, a skip under a requirement made by virtue of paragraph (1) shall comply with the requirement as soon as practicable, and if he fails to do so he shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 3 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) An officer authorised by the Department or a constable in uniform may remove or reposition a builder's skip or cause it to be removed or repositioned.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Where a skip has been removed under paragraph (3), the Department or, as the case may be, a police officer shall, where practicable, notify the owner of its removal, but if the owner cannot be traced, or if after a reasonable period of time after being so notified he has not paid any expenses recoverable from him under paragraph (5) and recovered the skip, the Department or a police officer may dispose of the skip and its contents.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Any expenses reasonably incurred by the Department or a police officer in the removal or repositioning of a skip under paragraph (3) or the disposal of a skip under paragraph (4) may be recovered from the owner of the skip.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) The Department or a police officer may retain any skip removed under paragraph (3) until any expenses recoverable by virtue of paragraph (5) in respect of the removal have been recovered.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(7) Any proceeds of such a disposal as is mentioned in paragraph (4) shall be used in the first place to meet the expenses reasonably incurred in the removal and disposal of the skip and its contents and thereafter any surplus shall be given to the person entitled thereto if known and if not shall be applied in the same manner as is provided for with respect to fines by section 20 of the Administration of Justice Act (Northern Ireland) 1954", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867811"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867811"}], ["F150"]}, ".\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(8) References in this Article to expenses incurred in the removal of a builder's skip shall include references to expenses incurred in storing the skip until it is recovered by the owner or, as the case may be, disposed of.\r"]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867811"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867811"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F150"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/apni/1954/9"}], ["1954 c. 9 (N.I.)"]}]}]}]}]}, {"a", [{"class", "LegAnchorID"}, {"id", "part-VIII"}], []}, {"div", [{"class", "LegClearPart"}], []}, {"h2", [{"class", "LegPart"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegPartNo"}], ["PART VIII", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegPartTitle"}], ["ROAD FERRIES"]}]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitleFirst"}], ["Interpretation of this Part", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-98"}], ["98."]}, "—(1) In this Part—\r"]}, {"ul", [{"class", "LegTabbed LegUnorderedList"}], [{"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“equipment” includes machinery, plant, apparatus and appliances;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“ferry landing place” means a place where vehicles, persons or goods may embark on or disembark from or (as the case may be) be loaded on or unloaded from a ferry vessel;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“ferry vessel” means a vessel used in the provision of a road ferry service;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“harbour authority” means any person in whom are vested, under any statutory provision other than this Part, functions of improving, maintaining or managing a harbour (within the meaning of the Harbours Act (Northern Ireland) 1970", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867821"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867821"}], ["F151"]}, ";\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“road ferry service” means a service for conveying vehicles, persons and goods by means of a vessel from a place on or near a road across water to another place on or near a road;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“road ferry undertaking” means the vessels, land, equipment, rights and other assets held for the purposes of, or in connection with, the provision of a road ferry service;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“vessel” includes a hovercraft within the meaning of the Hovercraft Act 1968", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867831"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867831"}], ["F152"]}, ".\r"]}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) For the purposes of this Part a ferry vessel or ferry landing place belongs to a road ferry service if it is used in the provision of that service.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) References in this Part (except Article 100) to a road ferry service are to a road ferry service provided by the Department under Article 99(1) or provided on behalf of the Department by another person in pursuance of any agreement under Article 99(2).\r"]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867821"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867821"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F151"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/apni/1970/1"}], ["1970 c. 1 (N.I.)"]}]}]}]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867831"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867831"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F152"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1968/59"}], ["1968 c. 59"]}]}]}]}]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Provision of road ferry services by, or on behalf of, the Department", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-99"}], ["99."]}, "—(1) Subject to the provisions of this Part, the Department may provide such road ferry services as it thinks fit.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) The Department may enter into an agreement with any person ( “the operator”) for the provision by that person on behalf of the Department of any road ferry service.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) An agreement under paragraph (2)—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["may provide for the leasing to the operator of any road ferry undertaking owned by the Department or any part thereof specified in the agreement;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["may contain such other terms and conditions as appear to the Department to be necessary to ensure the safe and proper provision of the road ferry service."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Except as provided by paragraph (5), where an agreement under paragraph (2) is in force, the operator shall, in relation to any road ferry service to which the agreement relates, have the same powers and duties and be subject to the same restrictions, liabilities and obligations as the Department has, or is subject to, in relation to a road ferry service provided by it.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Paragraph (4) does not apply to—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-5-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the power to issue directions under Article 101;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-5-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the power to make byelaws under Article 102;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-5-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the power to carry out works under Article 105;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-5-d"}], ["(d)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the power to dredge under Article 108;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-5-e"}], ["(e)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the power to acquire land under Article 110;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-5-f"}], ["(f)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["any other power, duty, restriction, liability or obligation excepted from that paragraph by an agreement under paragraph (2),"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["and any such power, duty, restriction, liability or obligation shall accordingly remain that of the Department alone.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) For the purposes of this Part the power to provide a road ferry service includes power—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-6-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["to establish, operate and manage that service;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-6-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["to provide vessels, buildings, equipment, facilities, amenities and services for the purposes of, or in connection with, that service;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-6-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["to maintain, operate, manage, repair, extend, alter, improve and renew anything mentioned in sub-paragraph (b); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-99-6-d"}], ["(d)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["to do anything which is necessary or appropriate for the purposes of, or in connection with, that service or which is incidental or ancillary to the provision of that service."]}, "\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Road ferry services provided otherwise than by, or on behalf of, the Department", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-100"}], ["100."]}, "—(1) The Department may enter into an agreement with the owner of any road ferry undertaking for the transfer to the Department, on such terms as may be agreed between the Department and the owner, of that road ferry undertaking.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) Paragraph (1) shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary in any local Act of Parliament or other instrument relating to the road ferry undertaking in question and any such Act or instrument shall, to the extent that it is inconsistent with any provision of this Part, cease to have effect on the date on which that undertaking is transferred to the Department under this Article.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) The Department may assist, financially or otherwise, the provision by any other person of a road ferry service.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Assistance under paragraph (3) shall be given on such terms and conditions as the Department thinks fit.\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Charges for road ferry services", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-101"}], ["101."]}, "—(1) There shall be payable in respect of the conveyance of vehicles, persons and goods on a ferry vessel belonging to a road ferry service such charges as may be specified in relation to that road ferry service in directions in writing issued by the Department in accordance with paragraphs (3) and (4).\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) A notice setting out the charges for the time being specified in directions under paragraph (1) in relation to a road ferry service shall be exhibited by the Department in a conspicuous place—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-2-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["in the vicinity of each ferry landing place belonging to that road ferry service; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-2-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["on each ferry vessel belonging to that road ferry service."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Where it proposes to issue directions under paragraph (1) in relation to a road ferry service, the Department shall—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["publish in at least one newspaper circulating in the locality in which the road ferry service is provided a notice—"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP4Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP4No"}, {"id", "article-101-3-a-i"}], ["(i)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP4Text"}], ["stating the effect of the proposed directions; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP4Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP4No"}, {"id", "article-101-3-a-ii"}], ["(ii)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP4Text"}], ["stating that, within such period as may be specified (not being a period of less than 30 days from the date of the publication of the notice) any person may by notice to the Department inform it of the grounds upon which he objects to the issuing of the directions;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["consider any objections received by it before the expiration of the period referred to in sub-paragraph (a); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-3-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["if it appears to the Department to be appropriate to do so, cause a local inquiry to be held."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) After considering—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-4-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["any objections to the proposed directions; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-101-4-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["where a local inquiry is held, the report of the person who held it,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["the Department may issue the directions, either without modifications or subject to such modifications as the Department thinks fit.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Any person who, with intent to defraud, travels on any ferry vessel without paying the charge payable by him in accordance with this Article, shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Byelaws in connection with road ferry services", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-102"}], ["102."]}, "—(1) The Department may make byelaws for any purpose in connection with the operation or management of a road ferry service, and in particular (but without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing) for all or any of the following purposes, namely—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-1-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for protecting persons, vehicles and goods on ferry vessels or land forming part of the road ferry undertaking from injury or damage;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-1-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for protecting vessels, land, equipment and other property forming part of the road ferry undertaking from damage;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-1-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for regulating the conduct of persons (including persons employed for the purposes of the road ferry service) on ferry vessels or land forming part of the road ferry undertaking;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-1-d"}], ["(d)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for regulating the embarkation, conveyance and disembarkation of persons, vehicles and goods;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-1-e"}], ["(e)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for maintaining order on ferry vessels and land forming part of the road ferry undertaking and preventing obstruction to the operation of the road ferry service."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) Any person who contravenes a byelaw made under this Article shall be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 2 on the standard scale.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Before making any byelaws under this Article the Department shall publish in at least two newspapers circulating in the locality in which the road ferry service is provided a notice—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["stating the intention of the Department to make the byelaws; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-102-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["specifying a place in that locality where a copy of the proposed byelaws may be inspected by any person free of charge at all reasonable hours during the period of 30 days from the date of the last publication of the notice."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) The Department shall not make the byelaws before the expiration of the period mentioned in paragraph (3)(b).\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Duty to provide timetable for, and notify disruption of, road ferry service", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-103"}], ["103."]}, "—(1) The Department shall publish in such manner as it thinks fit a timetable in connection with each road ferry service.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) Where for any reason it is necessary for the Department temporarily to discontinue or reduce a road ferry service, the Department shall—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-103-2-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["before any such discontinuance or reduction occurs, publish notice of the discontinuance or reduction in at least one newspaper circulating in the locality in which the road ferry service is provided; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-103-2-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["during the period when the road ferry service is discontinued or reduced, place such signs on roads in that locality as appear to the Department to be necessary to warn persons using those roads of the discontinuance or reduction."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Paragraph (2)(a) does not apply where, by reason of an emergency or other circumstances, it is impractical for notice to be given in accordance with that provision.\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Use of road ferry undertaking for other purposes", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-104"}], ["104."]}, "—(1) The Department may, to such extent as it thinks consistent with the requirements of a road ferry service—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-104-1-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["use any ferry vessel or other vessel belonging to that service; or"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-104-1-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["permit the use by any other person of any such vessel,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["for any other purpose in the locality in which that road ferry service is provided.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) The Department may by directions in writing specify the charges to be paid in respect of the use of a vessel under paragraph (1) and the use of a vessel under that paragraph shall be subject to such other terms and conditions as the Department thinks fit.\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Power of Department to carry out works", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-105"}], ["105."]}, "—(1) Subject to paragraphs (2) to (4), the Department may carry out such works as it considers appropriate for the purposes of, or in connection with, a road ferry service or the exercise of its functions under this Part.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) It shall be the duty of the Department, before carrying out any works within the limits within which a harbour authority may exercise its functions to consult with that authority and to take account of any representations made to the Department by that authority so as to ensure that the carrying out of those works causes the minimum interference to the property of that authority or to the exercise by that authority of its functions.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) The Department shall not construct, alter or extend any tidal work, except with the consent of—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-105-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the Secretary of State; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-105-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the Crown Estate Commissioners,"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["and subject to any conditions imposed by the Secretary of State or those Commissioners before the work is begun.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) Schedule 6 shall have effect in relation to any tidal work which is, or is to be, constructed, altered or extended by the Department.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) In this Article and Schedule 6—\r"]}, {"ul", [{"class", "LegTabbed LegUnorderedList"}], [{"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“the Secretary of State” means the Secretary of State concerned with navigation;\r"]}]}, {"li", [], [{"p", [{"class", "LegListTextStandard LegLevel3"}], ["“tidal work” means any work, or part of any work, which is on, under or over any land which is below the level of mean high water springs.\r"]}]}]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Application of 1847 Act to certain ferry landing places", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-106"}], ["106."]}, "—(1) The Harbour, Docks and Piers Clauses Act 1847", {"a", [{"class", "LegCommentaryLink"}, {"href", "#commentary-c16867841"}, {"title", "View the commentary text for this item"}, {"id", "reference-c16867841"}], ["F153"]}, " (except sections 6 to 13, 15 to 24, 37 to 42, 45, 49, 50, 54, 55, 66 to 68, 79 to 82, 84 to 90, 92, 97 and 98) shall, subject to the following provisions of this Article, apply to a ferry landing place which is not situated within, or immediately adjacent to waters within, the limits within which a harbour authority may exercise its functions as if—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-106-1-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["it were a harbour constructed in pursuance of an Act which incorporated that Act;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-106-1-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["this Part were the special Act for the purposes of that Act;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-106-1-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the Department were the undertakers for those purposes;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-106-1-d"}], ["(d)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["references to “the prescribed limits” were references to the limits specified under paragraph (2),"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2Text"}], ["and references in the following provisions of this Article and in Article 107 to the 1847 Act are references to that Act as applied by this paragraph.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) The Department may by order specify in relation to a ferry landing place mentioned in paragraph (1) the limits which are to be the prescribed limits for the purposes of the 1847 Act.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) Nothing in this Part or in any provision of the 1847 Act shall be construed as prejudicing the rights of any person who has an estate in land within any limits specified under paragraph (2).\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) The purposes for which byelaws may be made under section 83 of the 1847 Act shall include regulating the places within the limits specified under paragraph (2) in relation to a ferry landing place to which members of the public may be admitted, the times during which members of the public may be admitted to such places and the conduct of members of the public when so admitted.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) Paragraphs (2) to (4) of Article 102 shall apply to byelaws under section 83 of the 1847 Act as they apply to byelaws under that Article, but with the substitution in paragraph (3) for the reference to the road ferry service of a reference to the ferry landing place.\r"]}, {"div", [{"class", "LegAnnotations"}], [{"div", [{"class", "LegCommentaryItem"}, {"id", "commentary-c16867841"}], [{"p", [{"class", "LegCommentaryPara"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryType"}], [{"a", [{"href", "#reference-c16867841"}, {"title", "Go back to reference for this commentary item"}], ["F153"]}]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegCommentaryText"}], [{"a", [{"class", "LegCitation"}, {"title", "Go to item of legislation"}, {"rel", "cite"}, {"href", "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/1847/27"}], ["1847 c. 27"]}]}]}]}]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Functions of Department in relation to certain ferry landing places and surrounding limits", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-107"}], ["107."]}, "—(1) This Article applies to a ferry landing place mentioned in Article 106(1) and references in this Article to the limits of a ferry landing place are references to the limits specified under Article 106(2) in relation to that ferry landing place.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) The Department may enter into arrangements with any other person—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-107-2-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for the provision by that person, on land within the limits of a ferry landing place to which this Article applies, of any facilities, amenities or services;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-107-2-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["for the use by that person of such land for recreational or leisure activities."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) The Department shall at all times keep at appropriate places within the limits of a ferry landing place to which this Article applies a sufficient number of lifebuoys and lines in good order and fit and ready for use.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(4) The Department may by directions in writing specify the rate to be paid in respect of vessels entering the limits of a ferry landing place to which this Article applies; and references in the 1847 Act to rates shall be construed as references to rates for the time being specified under this paragraph.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(5) The Department may by directions in writing specify the charges to be paid in respect of the use by any person of equipment, facilities, amenities or services provided by the Department within the limits of a ferry landing place to which this Article applies.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(6) Paragraphs (3) and (4) of Article 101 shall apply to the issuing of directions under paragraph (4) or (5) of this Article as they apply to the issuing of directions under paragraph (1) of that Article, but with the substitution for references to the road ferry service of references to the ferry landing place.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(7) A notice setting out the rates for the time being specified in directions under paragraph (4) and the charges for the time being specified in directions under paragraph (5) shall be exhibited by the Department in a conspicuous place in the vicinity of the ferry landing place.\r"]}, {"h3", [{"class", "LegP1GroupTitle"}], ["Power to dredge", {"span", [{"class", "LegExtentRestriction"}, {"title", "Applies to Northern Ireland"}], [{"span", [{"class", "btr"}], []}, "N.I.", {"span", [{"class", "bbl"}], []}, {"span", [{"class", "bbr"}], []}]}]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP1ParaText"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegP1No"}, {"id", "article-108"}], ["108."]}, "—(1) The Department may, for the purpose of or in connection with any of its functions under this Part, dredge—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-108-1-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["any land owned by it;"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-108-1-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the foreshore and bed of any waters within any limits specified under Article 106(2); and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-108-1-c"}], ["(c)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["the foreshore and bed of any other waters over which a road ferry service is provided."]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(2) The powers in paragraph (1)(b) and (c) shall not be exercisable in relation to any part of the foreshore or the bed of waters under the management of the Crown Estate Commissioners except with the consent of, and subject to any conditions imposed by, the Crown Estate Commissioners.\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegP2ParaText"}], ["(3) The Department shall not deposit material dredged in a place below the level of mean high water springs except—\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-108-3-a"}], ["(a)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["with the consent of, and subject to any conditions imposed by, the Crown Estate Commissioners; and"]}, "\r"]}, {"p", [{"class", "LegClearFix LegP3Container"}], [{"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegLHS LegP3No"}, {"id", "article-108-3-b"}], ["(b)"]}, {"span", [{"class", "LegDS LegRHS LegP3Text"}], ["in such places and 